Random Walk Simulation

rwalk <- function(N) {
    result <- rep(NA, N)
    tail <- 0
    for (i in 1:N) {
        steps <- 1
        a <- if (runif(1) >= 0.5) 1 else -1
        while (a != 0) {
            steps <- steps + 1
            a <- a + if (runif(1) >= 0.5) 1 else -1
        }
        result[i] <- steps
    }
    result
}

Theory

The probability for returning to 0 for the first time after \(n\) steps is: \[ P(W = 2n) = {2(n-1) \choose n-1} \frac{1}{2^{2(n-1)}} \frac{1}{2n} \]

n = 1:128
a = choose(2*(n-1), n-1)/2^(2*(n-1))/(2*n)
x = c(0, 2*n)
w = c(0, cumsum(a))
plot(c(0, 400), c(0,1), type='n'); grid()
lines(x, w, col="darkgray", lwd=3)
lines(x_JS[1:150], w_JS[1:150], col="red")
abline(h = 0.95, col="gray")
